## When to use this component
Use the checkboxes component when you need to help users select multiple options from a list.

## When not to use this component
Do not use the checkboxes component if users can only choose one option from a list. In this case, use the [radios](/components/radios) component.

## How to use this component
Checkboxes are grouped within a [fieldset](/components/fieldset) which starts with a `<legend>` which lets the user know what they need to do.

## Variants

### Checkbox with input
This variant lets the user provide an answer other to the options in the list, or to provide additional information required to describe their answer.

Use this variation by wrapping the text field in a div with class `checkbox__other`, added directly after the checkbox label. CSS hides this field until the checkbox is `:checked`.

